ugs if they don't realize keys are case-sensitive, so I'm marking that as a must-have omission. The third token rule is demonstrated in the example but not explicitly stated, which makes it minor since it's inferrable from the code. The DI container footnote about loose coupling is also minor—it's more philosophical context than implementation-critical.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21528,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21528,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"94cb0b6b-4bd7-4619-8b99-b29d31267246","uuid":"e7343695-3b24-4b53-a447-a87d17ae1155"}
